articles.author: BILL BARROW and JILL COLVIN
articles.description: RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) — A presidential campaign that has careened through a felony trial, an incumbent president being pushed off the ticket and multiple assassination attempts comes down to a final sprint across a handful of states on Election Day eve.
articles.title: Harris and Trump are making a furious last-day push before Election Day

articles.author: CHRIS MEGERIAN
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — It's the election that no one could have foreseen. Not so long ago, Donald Trump was marinating in anger at Mar-a-Lago after being impeached twice and voted out of the White House.
articles.title: A presidential campaign unlike any other ends on Tuesday. Here's how we got here

articles.author: MATT BROWN and FREIDA FRISARO
articles.description: MIAMI (AP) — Concerts and carnivals hosted at polling precincts. “Souls to the Polls” mobilizations after Sunday service. And star-studded rallies featuring Hollywood actors, business leaders, musical artists and activists.
articles.title: Harris, Obamas and voting rights leaders work to turn out Black voters in run-up to Election Day

articles.author: JILL COLVIN and JONATHAN J. COOPER
articles.description: GASTONIA, N.C. (AP) — Donald Trump says he will be the “protector” of women, whether they like it or not.
articles.title: Trump wants to narrow his deficit with women but he's not changing how he talks about them

articles.author: STEVE PEOPLES
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Election Day is nearly upon us. In a matter of hours, the final votes in the 2024 presidential election will be cast.In a deeply divided nation, the election is a true toss-up between Democrat Kamala Harris and Republican Donald Trump.
articles.title: Here's what to watch as Election Day approaches in the U.S.

articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.description: Israel said Monday that it has terminated the agreement facilitating the work of the U.N. agency for Palestinian refugees, the main aid provider in Gaza, in what appeared to be a step to implement legislation passed last month that would sever ties with the agency and prevent it from operating in Israel.
articles.title: Middle East latest: Israel ends agreement with UN agency providing aid in Gaza

articles.author: JOSEPH WILSON
articles.description: BARCELONA, Spain (AP) — The recurrent storms in eastern Spain that led to massive flooding last week and killed at least 217 people, mostly near Valencia, dumped rain on Barcelona on Monday, prompting authorities to suspend commuter rail service.
articles.title: Heavy rains in Barcelona disrupt rail service as troops search for more flood victims in Valencia

articles.author: DAVID KOENIG
articles.description: Unionized factory workers at Boeing were voting Monday whether to accept a contract offer or to continue their strike, which has lasted more than seven weeks and shut down production of most Boeing passenger planes.
articles.title: Boeing machinists hold contract vote that could end their 7-week strike

articles.description: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) — A new tropical storm was expected to form Monday in the Caribbean and bring heavy rain to Jamaica and the Cayman Islands before strengthening to a hurricane and likely hitting Cuba, forecasters said.
articles.title: Storm in the Caribbean is on a track to likely hit Cuba as a hurricane

articles.author: HALELUYA HADERO
articles.description: It’s one of the most under-publicized policies of some of the biggest U.S. retailers: sometimes they give customers full refunds and let them keep unwanted items too.
articles.title: Many retailers offer 'returnless refunds.' Just don't expect them to talk much about it
